<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C5787FFC70868468EFA556424FA16" box="[648,850,1478,1501]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<collectionCode id="ED1AAE2BFFC70868468EFA5565B3FA16" box="[648,709,1478,1501]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/93c9-w2q7" name="University of Newcastle" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">NEW</collectionCode>
<collectionCode id="ED1AAE2BFFC7086846CDFA556424FA16" box="[715,850,1478,1501]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">SYNONYM</collectionCode>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436EEFFC70868450EF99C631CF9B2" blockId="40.[264,1323,1551,1817]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Based on an examination of 
<typeStatus id="54B0884CFFC70868465DF99C65EFF9E2" box="[603,665,1551,1577]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">types</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode id="ED1AAE2BFFC7086846AFF99C6472F9E2" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[681,772,1551,1577]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">USNM</collectionCode>
), it is obvious that Smith named the two sexes of this species as different species: ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC7086846C2F9A46475F99B" box="[708,771,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC7086846C2F9A46475F99B" box="[708,771,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Polia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC70868471EF9A4640DF99B" box="[792,891,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montara">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC70868471EF9A4640DF99B" box="[792,891,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">montara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the male and ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC708684050F9A463E3F99B" box="[1110,1173,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC708684050F9A463E3F99B" box="[1110,1173,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Polia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC7086840ACF9A4638DF99B" box="[1194,1275,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC7086840ACF9A4638DF99B" box="[1194,1275,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the female. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC7086845E4F9CC6545F9B3" box="[482,563,1631,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC7086845E4F9CC6545F9B3" box="[482,563,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears first, and I treat 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC70868475EF9CC64CDF9B3" box="[856,955,1631,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montara">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC70868475EF9CC64CDF9B3" box="[856,955,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">montara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436EEFFC70868453EF9146373F8D2" blockId="40.[264,1323,1551,1817]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
The fact that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC7086845DFF9146526F96B" box="[473,592,1671,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC7086845DFF9146526F96B" box="[473,592,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was misplaced in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC708684734F9146407F96B" box="[818,881,1671,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC708684734F9146407F96B" box="[818,881,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Polia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was pointed out by McCabe (
<number id="3DC324C9FFC7086840D8F9146268F96A" box="[1246,1310,1671,1697]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1980.0">1980</number>
). Based on the structure of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13302A6BFFC70868476AF93C64BBF902" box="[876,973,1711,1737]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 63" captionStartId="45.[264,362,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[292,1293,316,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[292,1294,316,1504]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 63. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 40, Protoperigea calientensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 41, Aseptis fanatica (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 42, Aseptis ethnica. 43, Aseptis ferruginea. 44, Aseptis torreyana (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 45, Aseptis serrula. 46, Apamea robertsoni (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 47, Apamea digitula (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 48, Apamea sordens. 49, Photedes sofiae. 50, Mammifrontia sarae (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 51, Mammifrontia rileyi (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 52, Benjaminola colorada (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 53, Perigonica tertia. 54, Perigonica fulminans. 55, Perigonica angulata. 56, Anarta fusculenta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 57, Anarta crotchi (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 58, Anarta oaklandiae. 59, Lasionycta sala (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 60, Trichocerapoda harbisoni (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 61, Trichocerapoda comstocki. 62, Trichocerapoda oceanis (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 63. Hexorthodes nipana." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273512/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC324C9FFC7086847ABF93C64BBF902" box="[941,973,1711,1737]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC7086847E8F93C6318F903" box="[1006,1134,1711,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC7086847E8F93C6318F903" box="[1006,1134,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits well into 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC70868450EF94466E8F93B" box="[264,414,1751,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC70868450EF94466E8F93B" box="[264,414,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Hexorthodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for which McDunnough (
<number id="3DC324C9FFC7086846D9F944646AF93A" box="[735,796,1751,1777]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1943.0">1943</number>
) designated 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC7086847B2F94463ADF93A" authority="Smith, 1900" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1900" box="[948,1243,1751,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC7086847B2F9446359F93B" box="[948,1071,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. serrata</emphasis>
(Smith, 
<number id="3DC324C9FFC708684091F94463A5F93A" box="[1175,1235,1751,1777]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1900.0">1900</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="54B0884CFFC70868450EF96C664CF8D2" box="[264,314,1791,1817]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
species. This species has very similar genitalia to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFC70868478FF96C6488F8D3" box="[905,1022,1791,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hexorthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipana">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFC70868478FF96C6488F8D3" box="[905,1022,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">H. nipana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
